SIMPLE: felicity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Felicity
<hw>Fe*lic"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Felicities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OE. <ets>felicite</ets>,
F. <ets>f⟦eacute⟧licit⟦eacute⟧</ets>, fr. L. <ets>felicitas</ets>, fr.
<ets>felix</ets>, <ets>-icis</ets>, happy, fruitful; akin to
<ets>fetus</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being happy;
blessedness; blissfulness; enjoyment of good.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our own <qex>felicity</qex> we make or find.</q>
<rj><qau>Johnson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Finally, after this life, to attain everlasting joy and
<qex>felicity</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Book of Common Prayer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which promotes happiness; a successful or
gratifying event; prosperity; blessing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>the <qex>felicities</qex> of her wonderful reign.</q>
<rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A pleasing faculty or accomplishment; <as>as,
<ex>felicity</ex> in painting portraits, or in writing or
talking</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Felicity</xex> of expression.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Bp. Warburton.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Happiness; bliss; beatitude; blessedness;
blissfulness. See <er>Happiness</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>felid</ent>⟦br⟧
